title: Grain mostly higher and livestock mixed
text:
Sat, Jul 11, 2015, 6:40 AM AEST - Australia Markets closed Grain mostly higher and livestock mixed Wheat lower, corn,oats and soybeans higher on the CBOT; beef lower and pork higher the CME. Associated Press – 44 minutes ago Recommend Print 
CHICAGO (AP) -- Grain futures were mostly higher Friday on the Chicago Board of Trade. 
Wheat for September delivery was off 2 cents to $5.76 a bushel; September corn was 6 cents higher at 4.3475 a bushel; December oats gained 1.75 cents at 2.6950 a bushel; while November soybeans gained 6.50 cents to $10.2225 a bushel. 
Beef was lower and pork was higher on the Chicago Mercantile Exchange. August live cattle was off 1 cent to $1.4747 a pound; August feeder cattle fell .50 cent to $2.1125 a pound; while August lean hogs were .38 cent higher to $.7365 a pound. @y7finance on Twitter, become a fan on Facebook US stocks surge on hopes for Greek breakthrough AFP
